# VoxelEngineUnity (Unity)

## Where to work

- Game C# lives under `Assets/Scripts/` (voxel engine in `Assets/Scripts/Voxel Engine/`, player in `Assets/Scripts/Player/`).
- Open the repo root that contains `Assets/`, `Packages/`, and `VoxelEngineUnity.slnx`.
- Default .NET solution: `VoxelEngineUnity.slnx`.

## Ignore when searching or editing

Do not treat generated or binary Unity output as source: `Library/`, `Temp/`, `Logs/`, `obj/`, `Build/`, `ProjectSettings/`, `UserSettings/`, and common asset binaries (textures, meshes, audio, etc.). Prefer `.cs` under `Assets/Scripts/`.

## File types

`.asset`, `.meta`, `.prefab`, and `.unity` files are YAML, not C#.

## Debugging

Use the **Attach to Unity** launch configuration (`vstuc`). Install the recommended extension: **Unity** (`visualstudiotoolsforunity.vstuc`). Set Unity’s external script editor to Cursor.

## Editor settings

Workspace editor settings, launch configs, and extension recommendations are in `.cursor/` (mirrored from `.vscode/`). Cursor also reads `.vscode/` for the same keys—keep both in sync if you change either folder.
